pageContext.claim: “I mean it's crazy. They're saying, oh, it's his home state. It's not his home state. He left you when he was 9, right?”
pageContext.analysis: Biden was born on Nov. 20, 1942 in Scranton. His father, Joseph Biden Sr., was a car dealership manager, but after a financial downturn in Scranton, struggled to find work. The Bidens moved out of their home in the city and moved in with the former vice president's maternal grandparents.Joe Sr. struggled to find work and the Bidens left Pennsylvania when "Joey" was in the fourth grade, and moved to Claymont, Delaware when he was 10 years old.
